WEBVTT

00:03.612 --> 00:05.657
[grand orchestral fanfare
playing]

00:26.417 --> 00:28.463
♪

00:34.121 --> 00:37.863
["Don't Let Me Be Misunderstood"
by Nina Simone playing]

00:37.907 --> 00:42.172
♪ Baby, you understand me now

00:44.653 --> 00:48.874
♪ If sometimes you see
that I'm mad ♪

00:50.833 --> 00:55.577
♪ Don't you know no one alive
can always be an angel? ♪

00:57.144 --> 01:02.279
♪ When everything goes wrong,
you see some bad ♪

01:02.323 --> 01:04.716
♪ But I'm just a soul

01:04.760 --> 01:09.547
♪ Whose intentions are good

01:09.591 --> 01:15.379
♪ Oh, Lord, please don't let me
be misunderstood ♪

01:20.515 --> 01:25.302
♪ You know, sometimes, baby,
I'm so carefree ♪

01:26.521 --> 01:31.743
♪ And then you're bound to see
my other side ♪

01:31.787 --> 01:34.877
♪ But I'm just a soul

01:34.920 --> 01:37.619
♪ Whose intentions are good

01:37.662 --> 01:39.490
[meowing]

01:39.534 --> 01:44.713
♪ Oh, Lord, please don't let me
be misunderstood. ♪

01:46.236 --> 01:48.847
Who the fuck are you?

01:51.111 --> 01:52.851
Me?

01:52.895 --> 01:54.723
I'm...

02:04.559 --> 02:06.126
[panting]

02:06.169 --> 02:07.910
-[slurping]
-[engine whirs]

02:07.953 --> 02:09.172
-[beeps]
-[horn honks]

02:09.216 --> 02:11.043
-[tool buzzing]
-[tapping keys]

02:11.087 --> 02:12.741
[sighs]

02:14.308 --> 02:16.353
[dog barking in distance]

02:19.269 --> 02:22.011
Come on! [groans]

02:22.054 --> 02:23.665
-Fuck!
-[horn honks]

02:23.708 --> 02:24.970
[egg cracks, sizzles]

02:25.014 --> 02:26.755
You missed the garbage.

02:27.756 --> 02:28.626
-[beeps]
-[tool buzzes]

02:28.670 --> 02:29.584
[taps key]

02:29.627 --> 02:32.326
[grunting, panting]

02:35.155 --> 02:37.026
-[beeps]
-[slurping]

02:38.027 --> 02:39.115
-[beeps]
-[horn honks]

02:39.159 --> 02:40.247
-[tapping]
-[tool buzzes]

02:40.290 --> 02:41.422
[dog barking in distance]

02:42.771 --> 02:43.946
-[beeps]
-[horn honks]

02:43.989 --> 02:44.903
-[tapping keys]
-[slurping]

02:44.947 --> 02:45.817
[tool buzzing]

02:45.861 --> 02:47.776
[dog barking in distance]

02:47.819 --> 02:49.560
[bed creaks]

02:51.519 --> 02:52.824
[panting]

02:52.868 --> 02:53.825
-[beeps]
-[taps key]

02:53.869 --> 02:55.697
-[sighs]
-[horn honks]

02:55.740 --> 02:57.829
-[tool buzzes]
-You missed the garbage.

02:58.787 --> 03:00.615
[beeps]

03:00.658 --> 03:02.007
-[tool buzzing]
-[tapping keys]

03:02.051 --> 03:03.879
[grunting, panting]

03:06.708 --> 03:08.057
[beeping]

03:08.100 --> 03:10.451
-[tool buzzing]
-[repeated beeping]

03:10.494 --> 03:12.540
[crickets chirping]

03:12.583 --> 03:14.455
[dog barking in distance]

03:20.461 --> 03:22.158
[sighs]

03:29.383 --> 03:31.428
[clattering in distance]

03:54.886 --> 03:56.932
[clattering in distance]

04:02.416 --> 04:04.461
♪

04:08.073 --> 04:10.119
[clattering nearby]

04:15.690 --> 04:17.735
[clattering continues]

04:33.142 --> 04:35.187
♪

04:37.320 --> 04:39.670
[line drones, button beeps]

04:39.714 --> 04:41.063
Put the phone down.

04:42.064 --> 04:43.413
We don't want any trouble.

04:43.457 --> 04:45.459
Your money. Cash.

04:45.502 --> 04:46.982
Now!

04:47.025 --> 04:50.899
Th-That's about all there is,
on that.

04:52.379 --> 04:53.815
That-that's it?

04:53.858 --> 04:56.557
I use a debit card.

04:56.600 --> 04:58.385
Jesus.

05:00.387 --> 05:02.084
MAN:
I didn't find anything.

05:02.127 --> 05:03.433
What about his watch?

05:03.477 --> 05:05.957
WOMAN:
Is this worth something?

05:06.001 --> 05:07.481
To me, it is.

05:07.524 --> 05:10.005
Take it.

05:15.489 --> 05:17.186
WOMAN:
Give me your ring.

05:17.229 --> 05:18.796
Give me your fucking ring!

05:18.840 --> 05:19.928
[running footsteps]

05:19.971 --> 05:21.538
-BRADY: Hey!
-[groaning]

05:21.582 --> 05:24.541
Hey! Hey, get off him! Now!

05:25.890 --> 05:27.631
Get off him! Get off him!

05:27.675 --> 05:29.590
I swear to God,
I'll fucking shoot you!

05:29.633 --> 05:30.852
BRADY:
Dad!

05:33.463 --> 05:35.857
-[groaning]
-WOMAN: Now!

05:35.900 --> 05:38.120
-Let him go, son.
-[Brady grunting]

05:39.077 --> 05:41.515
-What?
-[man gasping]

05:41.558 --> 05:43.604
I said let him go.

05:45.345 --> 05:47.042
[grunts]

05:48.348 --> 05:50.480
-Hey!
-What? What?

05:50.524 --> 05:52.221
BECCA:
Please stop.

05:52.264 --> 05:54.876
Just take what you want and go.
Please just...

05:54.919 --> 05:56.007
Just shut up!

05:56.051 --> 05:57.444
Let's get out of here.

05:59.010 --> 06:01.273
-Baby, let's go.
-[grunts in frustration]

06:01.317 --> 06:03.667
We picked the wrong
fucking house.

06:04.886 --> 06:07.105
-Just... fucking shit!
-Shut up.

06:10.457 --> 06:12.459
[golf club drops to floor]

06:13.547 --> 06:15.244
[lock clicks]

06:17.202 --> 06:19.248
What the fuck, Dad?

06:21.685 --> 06:23.644
♪

06:23.687 --> 06:25.733
[muffled, distorted chatter]

06:34.916 --> 06:37.092
HUTCH: I can't believe
I let this happen.

06:38.093 --> 06:40.051
My beautiful wife,

06:40.095 --> 06:43.141
beautiful kids, my home,

06:43.185 --> 06:45.317
broken into with a freaking...

06:45.361 --> 06:47.711
-Mr. Mansell.
-Excuse me?

06:47.755 --> 06:49.931
So, that's how they got in, huh?

06:49.974 --> 06:52.020
Using a pizza box?

06:52.063 --> 06:53.630
Yeah.

06:53.674 --> 06:55.371
And the golf club?

06:55.415 --> 06:57.025
Did you even take a swing?

06:57.068 --> 06:58.330
She had a, uh...

06:58.374 --> 07:00.463
Could've taken her, Dad.

07:00.507 --> 07:03.423
Look, you did the right thing,
Mr. Mansell.

07:08.210 --> 07:10.908
You know, if that was
my family... [chuckles]

07:14.346 --> 07:16.131
We're gonna get out
of your hair.

07:16.174 --> 07:19.656
You just leave that
garage door closed, okay?

07:27.229 --> 07:29.449
♪

07:29.492 --> 07:31.451
[car doors closing]

07:33.540 --> 07:35.542
[cars departing]

07:41.896 --> 07:43.506
[sighs]

07:43.550 --> 07:45.552
♪

08:08.183 --> 08:10.228
[sighs]

08:12.361 --> 08:14.406
[sighs]

08:21.849 --> 08:23.285
Hey, Dad.

08:23.328 --> 08:24.678
Hey, kiddo.

08:24.721 --> 08:27.245
-You couldn't sleep?
-No.

08:27.289 --> 08:28.464
Well...

08:28.508 --> 08:30.379
Oh. [exhales]

08:32.773 --> 08:34.557
You scared?

08:34.601 --> 08:37.778
Why would I be?
You're here.

08:37.821 --> 08:40.041
Yeah.

08:43.261 --> 08:45.089
Dad?

08:45.133 --> 08:46.264
Yeah?

08:46.308 --> 08:48.397
We need a cat.

08:48.440 --> 08:50.834
-Yeah?
-Yeah.

08:51.922 --> 08:53.924
Yeah.

08:53.968 --> 08:56.840
I was thinking the same thing.

09:02.542 --> 09:04.544
[garbage truck beeping,
rattling]

09:07.024 --> 09:08.504
[sighs]

09:10.898 --> 09:12.290
Come on!

09:12.334 --> 09:13.944
-[groans]
-[horn honking]

09:13.988 --> 09:15.163
Fuck!

09:15.206 --> 09:16.947
[panting]

09:21.561 --> 09:25.739
So, uh, I have to do a report
on a veteran for history class.

09:25.782 --> 09:27.741
Think I could just
interview you?

09:27.784 --> 09:28.742
[sizzling]

09:28.785 --> 09:31.179
Yeah, sure, son. Um...

09:31.222 --> 09:34.617
you know, I was an auditor,
so kind of a nobody.

09:34.661 --> 09:37.228
That makes for
a pretty dry story.

09:37.272 --> 09:39.622
Yeah, I-I really don't...
don't care.

09:39.666 --> 09:41.406
Just want to finish up
the project and call it a day.

09:41.450 --> 09:43.017
What about your uncle Charlie?

09:43.060 --> 09:44.584
He was a real soldier.

09:45.802 --> 09:47.195
I didn't mean it.

09:47.238 --> 09:49.023
Oh, your mom's right.

09:49.066 --> 09:50.677
Hey, you know what, uh,

09:50.720 --> 09:52.330
I actually already
left him a message.

09:53.331 --> 09:54.681
I'll try again later.

09:54.724 --> 09:56.552
Could try Grandpa.

09:56.596 --> 09:58.815
He actually saw some action.

09:58.859 --> 10:00.904
Yeah, maybe.

10:02.776 --> 10:04.342
HUTCH:
Have a great day.

10:04.386 --> 10:06.083
BECCA:
Oh, and, um...

10:06.127 --> 10:08.085
you missed the garbage.

10:10.697 --> 10:13.134
[sighs] I just...

10:14.701 --> 10:16.354
[Becca sighs softly]

10:18.705 --> 10:21.055
Oh, I took all the coffee.

10:21.098 --> 10:22.578
[chuckles]

10:24.841 --> 10:26.974
Have a good day, Hutch.

10:27.017 --> 10:28.715
Yeah, you, too.

10:28.758 --> 10:30.194
All right, kids, let's go.
Come on.

10:30.238 --> 10:32.109
Let's go.

10:38.202 --> 10:40.422
[door bangs open]

10:47.821 --> 10:49.866
[door closes]

10:54.479 --> 10:56.438
[engine rumbling]

10:56.481 --> 10:58.570
BECCA:
Put on your seat belt, okay?

10:58.614 --> 11:00.442
Hold on.

11:05.142 --> 11:06.709
[chuckling]:
Hey.

11:06.753 --> 11:09.190
Heard you had some excitement
last night.

11:09.233 --> 11:10.844
Yeah, it was just, uh...

11:10.887 --> 11:12.584
Man, I wish they'd have picked
my place, you know?

11:13.542 --> 11:16.719
Could've used the exercise.
[laughs]

11:17.938 --> 11:20.244
-[car engine starts]
-That's new.

11:20.288 --> 11:21.855
Pretty cool, huh?

11:21.898 --> 11:23.639
Yeah, the old man croaked.

11:23.683 --> 11:25.119
He didn't have much to leave,

11:25.162 --> 11:26.773
but at least I got
something out of it.

11:26.816 --> 11:28.209
Honey, come on.

11:28.252 --> 11:30.472
Got to go.

11:30.515 --> 11:32.779
-I'm sorry for your loss.
-[scoffs]

11:32.822 --> 11:35.346
There's nothing there
to mourn, man.

11:35.390 --> 11:37.087
Pretty slick, though, huh?

11:37.131 --> 11:40.525
The '72 Challenger,
4.9-liter V-8.

11:40.569 --> 11:45.182
Zero to 60 in...
I'm about to find the fuck out.

11:45.226 --> 11:47.837
[blaring over stereo]:
♪ You're a heartbreaker...

11:47.881 --> 11:49.883
[engine revs, tires squeal]

11:51.493 --> 11:54.539
-♪ You're a heartbreaker...
-[car speeds away]

11:55.584 --> 11:57.325
-[slurping]
-[engine whirs]

11:57.368 --> 11:58.500
-[beeps]
-[horn honks]

11:58.543 --> 12:00.807
[brakes squeal]

12:00.850 --> 12:02.591
[animal squeaking]

12:05.246 --> 12:08.031
-[indistinct chatter]
-[tool buzzing in distance]

12:09.293 --> 12:11.382
What do we got?
A rat or a possum?

12:11.426 --> 12:13.167
[grunts] Don't know.

12:20.174 --> 12:21.958
CHARLIE:
So...

12:22.002 --> 12:23.655
Good morning, Charlie.

12:23.699 --> 12:25.527
Did I hear right?

12:25.570 --> 12:27.877
Depends who you talked to.

12:27.921 --> 12:31.141
Well, your boy called.

12:31.185 --> 12:33.361
Then, yeah, you heard right.

12:35.842 --> 12:39.497
Now, he says that you had
the drop on one of them.

12:39.541 --> 12:41.935
Why didn't you take 'em out?

12:41.978 --> 12:43.632
I mean, shit...

12:43.675 --> 12:45.416
-[lid clicks]
-it's child's play.

12:45.460 --> 12:48.158
I was just trying to keep damage
to a minimum.

12:48.202 --> 12:49.899
Oh, yeah?
How's that working out for you?

12:49.943 --> 12:52.206
Everybody's safe, so...
Jesus!

12:53.337 --> 12:54.991
Don't worry.

12:55.035 --> 12:57.124
Safety's on.

12:58.647 --> 12:59.866
No, wait.

12:59.909 --> 13:02.303
-Oops. There.
-[safety clicks]

13:02.346 --> 13:04.392
There. See?

13:04.435 --> 13:07.830
Now, there's nothing that
turns out the lights right quick

13:07.874 --> 13:10.615
like a fucking bullet
to the brain, man.

13:10.659 --> 13:13.270
So... take it.

13:13.314 --> 13:15.272
I don't want it.

13:16.578 --> 13:18.623
It ain't a matter of want,
Hutch.

13:18.667 --> 13:20.451
It's the principle of need.

13:20.495 --> 13:24.586
So, keep my sister safe, bro.

13:29.809 --> 13:31.985
[Charlie shaking bottle]

13:33.551 --> 13:35.423
[sighs softly]

13:40.080 --> 13:42.125
[ice rattling]

13:57.358 --> 13:59.099
Hey.

14:00.317 --> 14:01.536
Oh, hey.

14:01.579 --> 14:03.799
Uh, I take it Becca called you.

14:03.843 --> 14:05.932
She did.

14:05.975 --> 14:08.630
And I'm thinking you did
the best thing you could.

14:10.023 --> 14:12.068
I mean, you being you.

14:12.112 --> 14:13.896
Yeah. I got you.

14:13.940 --> 14:16.943
Look, let's talk about you
wanting to buy this place.

14:16.986 --> 14:19.467
Do you really want to get rid
of me and Charlie that bad?

14:19.510 --> 14:20.903
Eddie, you're family.

14:20.947 --> 14:22.731
I just want you to enjoy
your retirement

14:22.774 --> 14:24.951
and Charlie his youth.

14:24.994 --> 14:27.214
It's a fair offer.

14:27.257 --> 14:30.173
But not a great one, you know.

14:30.217 --> 14:33.046
Look, I built this place up
from nothing with my hands.

14:33.089 --> 14:37.354
If I'm going to sell it,
then I want it to be a...

14:37.398 --> 14:39.269
goddamn great offer.

14:39.313 --> 14:40.923
-You know?
-Yeah.

14:40.967 --> 14:43.752
[chuckling]: What do you want
with this place, anyway?

14:44.753 --> 14:47.669
Guess I just want something
that's mine, you know?

14:48.757 --> 14:50.715
I do.

14:52.717 --> 14:54.763
Hey, Hutch.

14:55.764 --> 14:57.548
I'm rooting for you.

14:57.592 --> 14:59.072
[knocks on wall]

15:00.987 --> 15:02.989
♪

15:09.865 --> 15:11.606
[sighs]

15:12.607 --> 15:14.478
[clears throat]

15:15.436 --> 15:17.481
[tools buzzing]

15:35.021 --> 15:37.066
[indistinct broadcast plays
through static]

15:39.460 --> 15:41.505
[jazz music playing]

15:55.258 --> 15:56.956
-[music ends]
-HUTCH: Sounded good.

15:56.999 --> 15:59.132
HARRY [over radio]:
How long you been listening?

16:00.307 --> 16:02.874
Long enough to know you're
getting mighty good at that.

16:02.918 --> 16:05.051
[chuckling]: Shit.
When you're officially dead,

16:05.094 --> 16:07.705
got a lot of free time
on your hands, you know?

16:07.749 --> 16:09.577
Rough life.

16:09.620 --> 16:11.318
So, tell me about last night.

16:11.361 --> 16:12.362
[chuckles quietly]

16:12.406 --> 16:14.669
Word travels fast, huh?

16:14.712 --> 16:18.194
[over radio]: Look,
if they know, I know, you know?

16:19.717 --> 16:21.545
There were two of them.

16:21.589 --> 16:23.895
A man and a woman.

16:23.939 --> 16:26.724
Uh, late 20s, I'd say.

16:26.768 --> 16:28.944
[inhales deeply]

16:28.988 --> 16:31.816
[clicks tongue]
They were scared.

16:31.860 --> 16:33.514
Desperate.

16:33.557 --> 16:35.559
She had a gun.

16:35.603 --> 16:37.518
What kind?

16:37.561 --> 16:40.086
Uh, it was an old .38 Special.

16:40.129 --> 16:41.870
[sighs]

16:41.913 --> 16:44.003
Had electrical tape
on the handle.

16:44.046 --> 16:46.657
It was a Smith & Wesson.

16:46.701 --> 16:49.008
Hadn't been shot
in a long while.

16:50.096 --> 16:52.228
And it was, uh...

16:56.450 --> 16:58.756
...empty.

16:58.800 --> 17:01.803
-Seriously?
-Seriously.

17:01.846 --> 17:05.676
Hmm. Now I know why you
didn't do what you didn't do.

17:07.635 --> 17:09.376
What'd they get?

17:09.419 --> 17:12.509
HUTCH [chuckling]:
Not much. Just a couple bucks.

17:12.553 --> 17:15.512
HARRY: Well, I guess it
could've been worse, man.

17:15.556 --> 17:17.427
HUTCH:
Yeah.

17:17.471 --> 17:20.300
HARRY: Look, I know what
you're thinking about,

17:20.343 --> 17:22.389
and I wish you wasn't.

17:22.432 --> 17:25.609
Don't do nothing stupid.
You hear me?

17:29.352 --> 17:31.702
[snoring]

17:31.746 --> 17:33.791
[people whooping on TV]

17:36.794 --> 17:39.493
-[whooping continues]
-[gunfire]

17:44.585 --> 17:47.370
-Hey, Dad.
-[horse neighing on TV]

17:47.414 --> 17:50.025
-You been eating?
-What?

17:50.982 --> 17:52.941
[whirring]

17:52.984 --> 17:54.377
[bell dings]

17:54.421 --> 17:56.466
[gunfire on TV]

17:58.338 --> 18:00.209
You okay?

18:02.864 --> 18:04.866
I'm okay.

18:06.085 --> 18:08.087
You don't look okay.

18:12.526 --> 18:15.398
♪

18:15.442 --> 18:18.401
Do you remember who
we used to be, Hutchie?

18:18.445 --> 18:19.750
I do.

18:22.492 --> 18:24.451
[dogs barking in distance]

18:25.408 --> 18:27.454
♪

18:30.239 --> 18:32.285
[sighs]

18:36.376 --> 18:38.247
Hey, buddy.

18:38.291 --> 18:39.466
How was school?

18:39.509 --> 18:40.684
Fine.

18:40.728 --> 18:42.512
Hi, sweetheart.

18:42.556 --> 18:44.819
Come on. Help out.

18:44.862 --> 18:46.734
How was today?

18:46.777 --> 18:49.302
-It was what it was.
-I can't find it.

18:49.345 --> 18:51.304
-BECCA: Ugh.
-You can't find what?

18:51.347 --> 18:53.088
My kitty cat bracelet.

18:53.132 --> 18:54.481
Where was it?

18:57.136 --> 18:59.181
In here.

18:59.225 --> 19:03.185
They couldn't have stolen that,
would they?

19:04.230 --> 19:06.188
[sighs]

19:06.232 --> 19:08.756
♪

19:08.799 --> 19:11.280
BECCA: Honey, I'm sure
it'll turn up somewhere.

19:12.325 --> 19:14.283
[door bangs open]

19:18.505 --> 19:20.768
♪

19:20.811 --> 19:23.031
[snoring]

19:43.530 --> 19:46.054
Back so soon?

19:46.097 --> 19:48.012
Hey, Pop.

19:50.014 --> 19:53.931
There's this thing I got to do.

19:53.975 --> 19:56.586
Then you best go do it.

19:56.630 --> 20:00.329
["Life Is a Bitch"
by Luther Allison playing]

20:03.637 --> 20:05.726
♪ Life is a bitch

20:07.336 --> 20:09.599
♪ It's hurting me

20:12.254 --> 20:15.257
♪ Yes, I said life is a bitch,
y'all ♪

20:16.606 --> 20:19.305
♪ It's hurting me

20:22.090 --> 20:24.832
♪ You know my life is rough

20:24.875 --> 20:27.182
♪ Living in the street

20:27.226 --> 20:29.532
♪ Life is a bitch, y'all

20:29.576 --> 20:32.013
♪ Life is a bitch,
is a bitch on me ♪

20:35.799 --> 20:38.237
♪ Called my job

20:39.890 --> 20:42.589
♪ They might lay me off

20:44.808 --> 20:47.811
♪ Yes, I'm gonna call my job

20:49.335 --> 20:51.946
♪ They might lay me off

20:55.254 --> 20:57.691
♪ Three or four hungry babies

20:57.734 --> 21:00.084
♪ A starving lady

21:00.128 --> 21:02.348
♪ Too many worries

21:02.391 --> 21:05.960
♪ Too many bills
I gotta pay... ♪

21:06.003 --> 21:09.093
-[tattoo gun buzzing]
-[song continues quietly]

21:09.137 --> 21:10.921
-[door bangs shut]
-[buzzing stops]

21:13.794 --> 21:16.362
Agent Mansell, FBI.

21:17.667 --> 21:19.321
-[chuckles] That's old.
-I'm looking for...

21:19.365 --> 21:21.280
What?

21:21.323 --> 21:25.762
Your I.D.-- the badge expired
by about 20 years.

21:25.806 --> 21:28.461
Yeah, I'm pretty sure
that ain't you in the photo.

21:28.504 --> 21:29.984
So...

21:32.421 --> 21:33.596
Who are you?

21:37.296 --> 21:39.907
I'm just a man...

21:39.950 --> 21:41.996
who's looking for someone.

21:42.039 --> 21:43.998
Yeah, well,
you probably shouldn't

21:44.041 --> 21:46.261
flash cheese like that
around here, bro.

21:47.436 --> 21:51.353
There are three types of people
who, as you say, "flash cheese":

21:51.397 --> 21:52.963
people who don't know
any better,

21:53.007 --> 21:54.922
people who are seeking
to intimidate,

21:54.965 --> 21:57.751
and people like me, who wish
with every fiber of their being

21:57.794 --> 21:59.883
that someone would try
to take it from them.

22:04.758 --> 22:07.326
Uh...

22:09.980 --> 22:11.634
Thank you for your service.

22:14.289 --> 22:16.465
You, too, old-timer.

22:18.075 --> 22:21.209
[locks clicking]

22:22.819 --> 22:24.691
[heavy lock clunks]

22:30.174 --> 22:32.916
So, any takers?

22:37.486 --> 22:39.662
How can I help you?

22:39.706 --> 22:43.449
Send me in the direction
of this person.

22:48.454 --> 22:50.456
[thunder crashes]

22:52.980 --> 22:55.025
[whistling]

23:07.386 --> 23:09.388
[speaks Spanish]

23:19.789 --> 23:21.661
Luis.

23:30.670 --> 23:32.411
[yawns]

23:37.154 --> 23:39.200
♪

23:45.554 --> 23:47.600
[groaning, gasping]

23:49.384 --> 23:50.820
I speak. You listen.

23:50.864 --> 23:53.170
You know why I'm here.

23:53.214 --> 23:54.824
'Cause I'm a good man.

23:54.868 --> 23:56.435
I'm a family man.

23:56.478 --> 23:58.045
Most of all, I'm a man
who did not deserve

23:58.088 --> 24:00.526
your gun in his face.

24:00.569 --> 24:02.441
-Now, the watch.
-[Lupita whimpering]

24:07.707 --> 24:10.144
The kitty cat bracelet.

24:11.145 --> 24:13.495
What? I don't know
what the fuck you're...

24:13.539 --> 24:16.672
Give me the goddamn kitty cat
bracelet, motherfucker!

24:16.716 --> 24:18.282
I don't know what
you're talking about.

24:18.326 --> 24:19.893
I swear to God, I don't know.

24:19.936 --> 24:21.634
-The goddamn bracelet.
-I'll help you find it!

24:21.677 --> 24:23.636
Whoa, whoa, whoa, whoa.
Please, man.

24:23.679 --> 24:25.681
I don't know where it is!
Swear to God, I don't know.

24:25.725 --> 24:28.075
[baby screams, cries]

24:28.118 --> 24:30.164
[Lupita sobbing]

24:32.296 --> 24:34.168
[door creaks open]

24:38.128 --> 24:39.347
-LUPITA: Luis!
-[running footsteps]

24:39.390 --> 24:41.001
Hey, please just leave.

24:41.044 --> 24:43.003
-Please don't hurt us. Please.
-Please just leave.

24:44.439 --> 24:46.485
Fuck.

24:47.573 --> 24:49.575
♪

24:51.185 --> 24:53.013
[yells]

25:05.547 --> 25:07.506
[tires squeal]

25:07.549 --> 25:09.856
♪

25:09.899 --> 25:11.379
[tires squeal]

25:15.165 --> 25:16.819
[prolonged horn honking]

25:16.863 --> 25:19.169
[bus rattles, brakes hiss]

25:22.608 --> 25:24.610
[men laughing]

25:27.090 --> 25:29.658
[men laughing, groaning]

25:38.624 --> 25:40.626
Bus!

25:40.669 --> 25:43.498
-[men hollering]
-Bus!

25:43.542 --> 25:44.760
[excited chatter]

25:44.804 --> 25:46.283
-Bus!
-[hollering continues]

25:48.764 --> 25:51.245
HUTCH: They say
God doesn't close one door

25:51.288 --> 25:53.639
without opening another.

25:53.682 --> 25:56.424
[indistinct shouting, whooping]

25:56.467 --> 25:59.601
Please, God, open that door.

25:59.645 --> 26:03.431
["I've Gotta Be Me" by Steve
Lawrence & Eydie Gormé plays]

26:03.474 --> 26:06.216
♪ Whether I'm right

26:06.260 --> 26:08.958
-♪ Whether I'm wrong...
-[distorted]: Yeah!

26:09.002 --> 26:13.136
[distorted]: No, there's
no drinking on the bus.

26:13.180 --> 26:15.225
[distorted laughter]

26:15.269 --> 26:21.231
♪ I've gotta be me,
I've gotta be me ♪

26:21.275 --> 26:24.583
♪ What else can I be

26:24.626 --> 26:27.542
♪ But what I am?

26:27.586 --> 26:30.545
♪ I want to live

26:30.589 --> 26:33.809
♪ Not merely survive

26:33.853 --> 26:35.376
♪ And I won't give up...

26:35.419 --> 26:38.031
[distorted]:
Want a drink?

26:38.074 --> 26:40.511
Ooh, what do we have here?

26:40.555 --> 26:46.561
♪ I've gotta be me,
I've gotta be me ♪

26:46.605 --> 26:49.608
♪ Daring to try
to do it or die ♪

26:49.651 --> 26:54.264
♪ I've gotta be me

26:54.308 --> 26:56.310
♪

26:58.791 --> 27:00.531
♪ I can't be right...

27:00.575 --> 27:03.578
HUTCH: This girl's gonna
get home safe tonight.

27:04.971 --> 27:08.627
I hope these assholes
like hospital food.

27:08.670 --> 27:11.934
♪ I've gotta be me

27:11.978 --> 27:14.981
♪ Daring to try
to do it or die ♪

27:15.024 --> 27:22.771
♪ I've gotta be

27:22.815 --> 27:27.515
♪ Me...

27:27.558 --> 27:29.604
♪

27:33.173 --> 27:34.653
[song ends]

27:34.696 --> 27:36.437
A girl alone on a bus at night?

27:36.480 --> 27:38.265
-Just fucking stupid.
-It's stupid, right?

27:38.308 --> 27:40.354
Hey, guys, guys.

27:41.703 --> 27:44.097
What are you still doing here,
old man?

27:50.146 --> 27:52.627
I'm gonna fuck you up.

27:54.455 --> 27:56.805
[laughter]

27:56.849 --> 27:59.678
Yo. I got it. I got it.

28:00.548 --> 28:02.115
[grunting]

28:03.072 --> 28:04.117
[laughter]

28:04.160 --> 28:07.163
[grunting and groaning]

28:09.775 --> 28:11.951
[yelling]

28:13.692 --> 28:15.084
MAN:
Come on!

28:15.128 --> 28:17.391
[grunting and groaning continue]

28:30.360 --> 28:31.448
[gasps]

28:33.102 --> 28:34.451
[screams]

28:34.495 --> 28:36.584
[grunting]

28:44.200 --> 28:45.767
[man coughs]

28:45.811 --> 28:47.813
-[panting]
-[men groaning]

28:49.815 --> 28:51.817
[panting, groaning]

29:00.347 --> 29:01.914
MAN:
Shit.

29:02.915 --> 29:04.960
[pained grunting]

29:08.572 --> 29:11.010
[strained grunting]

29:12.185 --> 29:14.143
[knife squishing]

29:15.101 --> 29:16.145
[screams]

29:16.189 --> 29:18.495
[grunting]

29:19.758 --> 29:22.586
[man yells]

29:24.893 --> 29:26.547
Oh, fuck!

29:26.590 --> 29:29.245
[grunting and groaning continue]

29:30.246 --> 29:31.595
[bell dinging repeatedly]

29:38.472 --> 29:39.995
[woman screams]

29:41.388 --> 29:43.433
[panting]

29:44.391 --> 29:46.436
[groaning]

29:47.611 --> 29:49.309
[speaks Russian]
...nose!

29:49.352 --> 29:51.224
What the fuck are you saying?

29:51.267 --> 29:53.095
Nose is broken!

29:54.096 --> 29:56.011
My fucking teeth.

29:56.055 --> 29:57.926
[groaning]

29:57.970 --> 29:59.885
-Is it bad?
-It's bad.

29:59.928 --> 30:01.582
Fuck!

30:02.931 --> 30:04.977
[groaning quietly]

30:08.458 --> 30:10.417
[men coughing, groaning]

30:10.460 --> 30:12.419
MAN:
Your arm is fucked up.

30:12.462 --> 30:14.290
Who the fuck is this guy?

30:14.334 --> 30:16.379
DRIVER:
Man, are you...

30:17.554 --> 30:19.295
MAN:
Fucked up.

30:19.339 --> 30:21.341
[grunts]

30:21.384 --> 30:23.560
[gruff panting]

30:33.744 --> 30:35.877
HUTCH:
Run.

30:35.921 --> 30:37.705
[footsteps]

30:37.748 --> 30:40.012
WOMAN:
Thank you.

30:42.405 --> 30:44.494
[yelling]

30:44.538 --> 30:46.496
[grunting and groaning]

30:46.540 --> 30:48.585
♪

30:56.506 --> 30:58.552
[grunting and groaning continue]

31:08.040 --> 31:10.085
[men groaning, gasping]

31:13.697 --> 31:15.482
[thuds]

31:16.962 --> 31:18.833
[grunts]

31:18.877 --> 31:20.182
[shouts indistinctly]

31:20.226 --> 31:22.097
[grunting and groaning]

31:22.141 --> 31:24.404
[gasping]

31:27.624 --> 31:29.017
[pole clangs on floor]

31:29.061 --> 31:31.106
[gasping, gurgling]

31:34.109 --> 31:35.502
[grumbles]

31:38.070 --> 31:40.072
[grunts]

31:45.991 --> 31:47.949
[cup drops to floor]

31:59.134 --> 32:01.180
[air hissing through straw]

32:04.923 --> 32:06.925
Sorry about the mess.

32:08.927 --> 32:10.929
♪

32:37.346 --> 32:39.392
-Hey.
-Hey.

32:41.568 --> 32:43.613
I couldn't sleep.

32:45.702 --> 32:47.748
Where'd you go?

32:56.670 --> 32:58.367
[Becca gasps]

33:00.804 --> 33:03.024
Yeah.

33:03.068 --> 33:05.113
It's been a hell of a day.

33:06.201 --> 33:08.987
I can see that.

33:10.249 --> 33:12.381
HUTCH:
Just like old times, huh?

33:12.425 --> 33:14.688
-BECCA: Mm-hmm.
-[Hutch hisses in pain]

33:16.081 --> 33:18.039
[exhales]

33:18.083 --> 33:21.042
[inhales sharply, exhales]

33:21.086 --> 33:23.088
I miss you.

33:25.655 --> 33:27.614
I'm right here, Hutch.

33:27.657 --> 33:29.659
I'm always right here.

33:30.747 --> 33:32.532
I know.

33:36.666 --> 33:39.321
Tonight...

33:39.365 --> 33:41.454
I was thinking...

33:41.497 --> 33:43.195
About what?

33:44.196 --> 33:46.807
HUTCH:
About...

33:46.850 --> 33:49.418
Becca. [groans]

33:49.462 --> 33:51.507
[hisses in pain]

33:53.074 --> 33:57.644
How we haven't embraced
in far too long.

33:57.687 --> 34:02.083
We haven't shared a kiss in...
I don't know.

34:02.127 --> 34:05.913
We haven't had sex in months.

34:05.956 --> 34:10.570
We haven't made love in years.

34:12.485 --> 34:14.791
You seem so far away.

34:16.010 --> 34:21.189
I know that's... it's unfair
to put it like that, but...

34:21.233 --> 34:23.757
I just...

34:23.800 --> 34:26.064
I-I miss you.

34:37.205 --> 34:39.686
[sighs]
Remember who we used to be?

34:43.168 --> 34:44.995
I do.

34:48.782 --> 34:50.827
♪

35:02.100 --> 35:04.754
-[crickets chirping]
-[dog barking in distance]

35:20.335 --> 35:22.381
♪

35:37.787 --> 35:40.703
♪

35:45.099 --> 35:47.057
[tires squealing]

35:47.101 --> 35:49.147
[horn honks]

35:51.584 --> 35:53.629
[tires screech]

36:05.511 --> 36:07.469
[tires squealing]

36:07.513 --> 36:09.341
[horns honking]

36:09.384 --> 36:12.170
MAN:
All right, man, there he is!

36:13.823 --> 36:15.521
Hi.

36:19.481 --> 36:21.440
[chatter in Russian]

36:21.483 --> 36:24.225
[upbeat pop music playing]

36:24.269 --> 36:26.271
[woman singing in Russian]

36:33.539 --> 36:35.584
On the house, sir.

36:38.979 --> 36:41.634
[inhales sharply, grunts]

36:51.121 --> 36:53.428
[snorts]

36:56.039 --> 36:57.998
[cheering]

36:58.041 --> 37:00.087
[continues singing in Russian]

37:14.884 --> 37:16.930
[singing in Russian]

37:30.813 --> 37:32.859
[applause]

37:39.953 --> 37:41.998
[woman resumes singing]

37:43.478 --> 37:45.088
Ah.

37:47.352 --> 37:49.354
[chatter in Russian]

37:51.138 --> 37:52.792
[chuckles]

38:14.988 --> 38:17.033
[laughter]

38:59.728 --> 39:01.339
[woman continues singing
in Russian]

39:03.602 --> 39:06.126
-[groaning]
-[onlookers scream and gasp]

39:18.181 --> 39:20.183
-[slashing]
-[body thuds]

39:41.335 --> 39:42.380
[sighs]

39:52.520 --> 39:54.566
[cell phone ringing]

40:01.399 --> 40:03.401
[medical monitor beeping]

40:04.750 --> 40:06.404
[Yulian sniffs]

40:14.412 --> 40:16.414
Will he walk again?

40:17.458 --> 40:20.461
DOCTOR: Sir, we are
monitoring his vitals,

40:20.505 --> 40:23.638
but the damage
to his brain is...

40:44.006 --> 40:46.139
WOMAN [over P.A.]:
Dr. Mendez to Critical Care.

40:46.182 --> 40:47.445
Dr. Mendez.

40:49.882 --> 40:51.492
[door opens]

40:51.536 --> 40:53.886
Yulian...
[groans, gasps]

40:54.930 --> 40:57.150
Who did this to my brother?

40:57.193 --> 40:58.804
[panting]:
There was a man.

40:58.847 --> 41:00.501
He attacked us unprovoked.

41:00.545 --> 41:02.895
One man?
Are you fucking with me?

41:02.938 --> 41:04.505
-No, sir. No, sir!
-Don't you lie to me!

41:04.549 --> 41:07.508
-Don't you fucking lie to me!
-[screaming]

41:07.552 --> 41:09.336
Don't you...

41:09.379 --> 41:11.338
Don't you lie to me!

41:11.381 --> 41:13.296
Don't you fucking lie to me!

41:13.340 --> 41:15.081
I'm not lying to you. I swear.

41:15.124 --> 41:17.562
[muffled grunt]

41:17.605 --> 41:19.346
MAN:
Yulian?

41:20.347 --> 41:21.870
Please don't get more mad.

41:24.699 --> 41:26.484
You hated Teddy.

41:30.923 --> 41:34.535
Your words may be correct,

41:34.579 --> 41:36.885
but they are no less unwise.

41:48.680 --> 41:50.464
[sniffs]

41:50.508 --> 41:53.249
How can I find this man?

41:53.293 --> 41:55.295
[man straining]

41:56.949 --> 42:00.300
[Tchaikovsky's "Piano Concerto
No. 1 in B-flat Minor" playing]

42:10.266 --> 42:12.312
[whistling melody]

42:13.531 --> 42:15.533
-[music stops]
-[whistling continues]

42:19.493 --> 42:21.147
-Mmm.
-BRADY: Morning.

42:22.148 --> 42:24.150
Morning.

42:24.193 --> 42:25.934
What happened to you?

42:25.978 --> 42:27.588
Hmm?

42:27.632 --> 42:29.372
Dad, you look like shit.

42:29.416 --> 42:31.723
You should see the other guys.

42:31.766 --> 42:33.681
When you made that tackle,

42:33.725 --> 42:36.641
that was a good takedown.

42:36.684 --> 42:39.252
You had my back,
and I'm proud of you.

42:40.296 --> 42:41.428
-[phone ringing]
-BECCA: Morning.

42:41.471 --> 42:43.386
Morning.

42:45.040 --> 42:46.389
[clears throat]

42:46.433 --> 42:47.826
Hutch here.

42:47.869 --> 42:51.090
HARRY:
Last night, that was you, huh?

42:51.133 --> 42:53.614
I thought we said no landlines.

42:53.658 --> 42:56.138
Relax. I got 30 seconds.

42:56.182 --> 42:57.618
Okay, well, go.

42:57.662 --> 43:01.056
So, how did it feel?

43:01.100 --> 43:03.058
[chuckles]
Like salvation day.

43:03.102 --> 43:05.278
Yeah, I bet.

43:05.321 --> 43:08.629
Look, I'm happy that your
relapse made you feel so good,

43:08.673 --> 43:11.240
-but, man, you got
a fucking problem. -Yeah?

43:11.284 --> 43:14.504
One of those guys was the
brother of Yulian Kuznetsov,

43:14.548 --> 43:16.419
and you don't want
to fuck with him, Hutch.

43:16.463 --> 43:18.900
I'm serious.
Ask The Barber. He knows.

43:18.944 --> 43:21.033
It was an isolated incident,
sir.

43:21.076 --> 43:22.861
Yulian Kuznetsov.
Ask The Barber.

43:22.904 --> 43:24.645
BECCA:
Who was that?

43:24.689 --> 43:26.386
Just a distributor of ours.

43:26.429 --> 43:28.083
Hey, I have an idea.

43:28.127 --> 43:30.346
How about I make that lasagna
that you love tonight?

43:30.390 --> 43:32.653
You know, from scratch,
like I used to.

43:32.697 --> 43:34.742
-It's been a while.
-Lasagna!

43:34.786 --> 43:36.875
-[chuckles]
-I'd really like that.

43:36.918 --> 43:39.051
[engines whirring]

43:39.094 --> 43:40.835
[tools buzzing]

43:45.623 --> 43:47.537
[cell phone vibrates]

43:55.110 --> 43:57.025
[sighs]

43:57.069 --> 44:01.551
♪ I told myself a lie

44:02.683 --> 44:05.468
♪ When I said

44:05.512 --> 44:09.211
♪ I had no cares

44:10.952 --> 44:13.738
♪ 'Cause when I'm alone

44:13.781 --> 44:15.478
♪ All alone

44:15.522 --> 44:18.264
♪ Out come the tears...

44:18.307 --> 44:19.700
Gentlemen.

44:19.744 --> 44:22.877
Mr. Mansell.

44:22.921 --> 44:25.445
It has been some time.

44:26.620 --> 44:28.274
That it has.

44:28.317 --> 44:31.973
What, pray tell,
may we do for you, good sir?

44:32.017 --> 44:35.934
What can you tell me
about Yulian Kuznetsov?

44:40.590 --> 44:44.769
Am I really now
that predictable?

44:44.812 --> 44:47.989
From where I sit, Mr. Mansell,

44:48.033 --> 44:50.426
everyone is.

44:50.470 --> 44:54.517
Short story long,
he's as bad as they come.

44:54.561 --> 44:58.608
A connected, funded sociopath

44:58.652 --> 45:01.437
with resources
to make things complicated.

45:04.310 --> 45:06.138
So, he's a bad guy?

45:12.013 --> 45:14.668
-Has he got any hobbies?
-Collects art,

45:14.712 --> 45:17.018
to the tune of eight
and nine figures.

45:18.237 --> 45:19.368
Anything good?

45:19.412 --> 45:20.543
Fuck if I know.

45:20.587 --> 45:22.415
But what I do know is,

45:22.458 --> 45:24.504
if he doesn't know
who you are yet,

45:24.547 --> 45:25.766
he will soon.

45:25.810 --> 45:28.856
What have you got for me?

45:28.900 --> 45:31.076
I found his dad.

45:31.119 --> 45:33.252
He's got him at
a nursing home downtown.

45:33.295 --> 45:35.558
That's not much.

45:35.602 --> 45:37.473
I wouldn't worry
about this Hutch guy.

45:37.517 --> 45:40.259
Your man here looks to be
as vanilla as they come.

45:40.302 --> 45:45.525
If you can't recognize a wolf
in sheep's clothing,

45:45.568 --> 45:49.659
I question the viability
of your employment here.

45:49.703 --> 45:52.488
I have a friend at the Pentagon.

45:52.532 --> 45:54.055
I'll keep looking.

45:55.013 --> 45:57.929
One blackmail package coming up.

46:06.241 --> 46:08.504
What the fuck?

46:08.548 --> 46:10.593
[typing]

46:12.726 --> 46:14.162
What?

46:14.206 --> 46:15.337
THE BARBER:
And if he can't take care

46:15.381 --> 46:16.904
of a loose end like you,

46:16.948 --> 46:20.255
he'd have to give up
his share of the Obshak.

46:21.256 --> 46:23.302
The Obshak?

46:25.434 --> 46:27.219
Think of it like the 401[k]

46:27.262 --> 46:29.656
of the Russian mob.

46:29.699 --> 46:31.963
That's hundreds of millions
of dollars in cash

46:32.006 --> 46:33.965
perpetually on the move,

46:34.008 --> 46:37.490
and Yulian is
the current babysitter.

46:37.533 --> 46:40.536
That said, he's more than
a bit weary of this life.

46:40.580 --> 46:42.800
I think, if he had his way,
he'd probably walk away.

46:46.716 --> 46:49.110
[elevator bell chimes]

47:05.170 --> 47:06.780
[typing]

47:06.824 --> 47:08.695
[computer chimes]

47:14.919 --> 47:16.746
I'm out. No need to pay.

47:16.790 --> 47:18.661
Good luck.

47:24.363 --> 47:26.278
[sighs]

47:29.803 --> 47:32.110
-BECCA: It's beautiful.
